17:23.840 --> 17:25.320
of person.

17:25.320 --> 17:29.680
And everybody is of the opinion that if we are going to catch up in the United States,

17:29.680 --> 17:36.200
we must treat our scientists better, pay them more respect, and know the importance of

17:36.200 --> 17:38.200
the work that they are doing.

17:38.200 --> 17:43.440
Hundreds of years ago, one of these so-called dreamers was named Isaac Newton.

17:43.440 --> 17:46.960
He wanted to know what makes the rock fall when you throw it up.

17:46.960 --> 17:52.080
He developed a theory of gravity, and today every high school boy and girl of course knows

17:52.080 --> 17:54.880
about Newton's laws of gravity.

17:54.880 --> 18:01.360
If it hadn't been for his curiosity and of those who followed after him, then these missiles

18:01.360 --> 18:05.240
never would have been possible because it's the law of gravity that has a whole lot to

18:05.240 --> 18:11.760
do but how we are going to be able to enter into conquer and find out about space.

18:11.760 --> 18:17.760
And how our scientists today are going to be able to compete successfully in this space

18:17.760 --> 18:19.040
age.

18:19.040 --> 18:26.080
