in the effort to gain the control of space to at least get on an equal basis.

21:35.440 --> 21:40.800
I think the reasons that we have gotten behind are not just the absence of the lack of money

21:40.800 --> 21:44.880
but we haven't had the organization, we haven't had the responsibility, we haven't given

21:44.880 --> 21:49.600
it enough emphasis for the government and among our people.

21:49.600 --> 21:55.680
We must also inaugurate new and thoughtful policies and programs to regain the political

21:55.680 --> 22:02.000
and the economic leadership among the peoples of the world particularly in the free world.

22:02.000 --> 22:07.640
Furthermore I think we must take steps to see that our economy remains stable and vital

22:07.640 --> 22:11.000
here in the United States itself.

22:11.000 --> 22:15.680
Along with several other senators I joined in to introduction of legislation this week

22:15.680 --> 22:20.160
which would alleviate some of the distress that has come to the small farmers and to the

22:20.160 --> 22:22.440
people in West Tennessee particularly.

22:22.440 --> 22:27.840
Whereas the result of the rain and the floods of last year they lost their crops and that

22:27.840 --> 22:34.560
certainly they need secure loans in order to get that enable them to continue on as farmers

22:34.560 --> 22:37.480
and continue on in our economy.

22:37.480 --> 22:43.000
This Congress convened and moved to meet the problems of the day and this connection I think

22:43.000 --> 22:48.120
with President Eisenhower stated the union message was the best address that he has made

22:48.120 --> 22:49.120
during his career.

22:49.120 --> 22:54.800
He had set forth general programs that most all Americans can agree with.

22:54.800 --> 22:59.120
Most impressive was his expression of the peaceful intentions of the people of the United

22:59.120 --> 23:00.120
States.

23:00.120 --> 23:07.600
His emphasis on improved world trade, on economic assistance, on people to people contacts

23:07.600 --> 23:11.000
but his vigorous call for disarmament.

23:11.000 --> 23:15.800
The force will put plea for peace if followed up and implemented and fought for in the Congress

23:15.800 --> 23:20.280
of the United States and do much to win back to us.

23:20.280 --> 23:24.320
Many of the friends that we have lost during the last few years as a result of having no

23:24.320 --> 23:30.320
policy are as a result of vacillating about what we are going to do.

23:30.320 --> 23:34.280
I feel that the Congress will cooperate with the President in trying to get these things

23:34.280 --> 23:35.280
done.

23:35.280 --> 23:37.120
We will all work toward that end.

23:37.120 --> 23:39.160
I will be back with you next week.

23:39.160 --> 23:40.160
Thank you very much.

23:40.160 --> 24:01.120
Ladies and gentlemen, friends of Tennessee, the Preparedness Subcommittee of the United

24:01.120 --> 24:08.080
States Senate of which Senator Lyndon Johnson is chairman and with seven or eight members

24:08.080 --> 24:13.520
of Republicans and Democrats have just completed the hearings which were commenced shortly

24:13.520 --> 24:18.600
after the launching of the first sputnik by the Soviet Union.

24:18.600 --> 24:23.200
As Deputy Chairman of that committee, I am most regular attendant and a person who has

24:23.200 --> 24:28.560
been tremendously interested in the work of the committee, is I are distinguished neighbor,

24:28.560 --> 24:32.080
the senator from Mississippi, Senator John Stennis.

24:33.080 --> 24:40.120
He is here today to talk with us about the whole missile program and about the work

24:40.120 --> 24:41.600
of this Preparedness Subcommittee.

24:41.600 --> 24:46.480
Certainly, I am glad to have you here, John.

24:46.480 --> 24:50.480
Tell us what you think about the accomplishments of the committee.

24:50.480 --> 24:51.480
Well, let's decide.

24:51.480 --> 24:55.440
First want to say that I certainly enjoyed sitting by you during all these hearings where

24:55.440 --> 25:01.280
we all had the benefit of your fine knowledge of national as well as international affairs.

25:02.280 --> 25:04.800
We've sat in that work together.

25:04.800 --> 25:14.040
I've been impressed tremendously by the fact that we have great military power now, our

25:14.040 --> 25:18.840
feet of two long range bombers and other striking power.

25:18.840 --> 25:20.600
I think we are superior now.

25:20.600 --> 25:24.200
We could meet any threat that might be thrown at us.

25:24.200 --> 25:29.640
Second, that within two or three years from now, unless we close the gap on this missile

25:30.640 --> 25:36.640
program and catch up, we could well be a secondary military power and that means that

25:36.640 --> 25:39.640
we have to take time, we wouldn't want to take it.

25:39.640 --> 25:43.640
Now, in all these hearings, that's one of my points and all these hearings I'd just

25:43.640 --> 25:49.640
like to ask you what some of their things impressed you so in an outstanding way.

25:49.640 --> 25:55.140
Well, one thing I was impressed was, and that is that on Thursday at the conclusion of

25:55.140 --> 26:01.100
the hearing, Senator Lyndon Johnson presented a statement which was agreed to unanimously

26:01.100 --> 26:04.420
by all of the members of the committee.

26:04.420 --> 26:09.180
That is, while things might have been different, different decisions have been made in years

26:09.180 --> 26:15.140
passed by both Democratic and Republican administrations, we're not concerned about the task, but

26:15.140 --> 26:18.140
where we are going to go from here.

26:18.140 --> 26:24.340
And I felt that in the long range of ballistic missiles and also the intermediate ballistic

26:24.340 --> 26:31.620
missiles, that the Soviet Union was ahead of us at present time, that we are ahead as far

26:31.620 --> 26:35.660
as the air force is concerned, but they are increasing their rate.

26:35.660 --> 26:38.620
Did you find that, do you think that's generally true?

26:38.620 --> 26:41.180
Yes, I think that's generally true.

26:41.180 --> 26:48.180
And another thing that impressed me was that even though our scientists are fine and outstanding,

26:48.180 --> 26:55.180
that these Russians have made tremendous headway and they train more minds in that direction,

26:55.180 --> 27:02.180
and therefore that contributes to a better system of concentrating and producing these

27:02.180 --> 27:05.180
terrible weapons and missiles as well as others.

27:05.180 --> 27:11.180
In other words, in our education that they have put more stress on scientists and physicists

27:11.180 --> 27:15.780
and engineers than we have, and that if we're going to catch up and stay ahead by more

27:15.780 --> 27:20.340
of our young people are going to have to have scientific education, then we're going

27:20.340 --> 27:24.060
to have to look at scientists more and more friendly way, aren't we?

27:24.060 --> 27:28.540
We're going to have to find that talent, yes, and look at them in a more friendly way

27:28.540 --> 27:30.540
and an honest standing way and another thing.

27:30.540 --> 27:34.780
Well, I wonder if you were impressed as I was, however, that since the beginning of the

27:34.780 --> 27:39.980
hearings that we actually have made considerable progress in getting started.

27:39.980 --> 27:42.020
Oh, yes, I've been throughout learning some of the things.

27:42.020 --> 27:44.540
Well, I think we've made tremendous progress.

27:44.540 --> 27:50.380
The Department of Defense has been eluded and they've stepped up our long-range missiles,

27:50.380 --> 27:54.780
our intermediate range missiles as much as they possibly can.

27:54.780 --> 27:58.180
They've taken off their overtime restrictions.

27:58.180 --> 28:01.100
Now a satellite program is not a failure.

28:01.100 --> 28:03.980
This Vanguard matter was just one experiment.

28:03.980 --> 28:07.380
After all, that's not a failure by any means.

28:07.380 --> 28:09.780
We are getting in motion on more front side.

28:09.780 --> 28:17.540
I'm anxious that we step up our submarine program more and also step up their B-52 bombers

28:17.540 --> 28:23.180
including that long-range, manless bomber that we have which is a missile itself.

28:23.180 --> 28:28.100
Yes, and ladies and gentlemen, all of us on the committee and Senator Stenner's certainly

28:28.100 --> 28:34.260
feel that while we want to catch up insofar as missiles and weapons and air force,

28:34.260 --> 28:39.700
that eventually we want to try to work toward peace for the same determination that we are

28:39.700 --> 28:42.420
working to prepare ourselves against any attack.

28:42.420 --> 28:45.860
Certainly a pleasure to have Senator Stenner's Willis on this program.

28:45.860 --> 28:46.860
We thank a lot of you.

28:46.860 --> 28:47.860
Thank you, Senator.

28:47.860 --> 28:48.860
I know.

28:48.860 --> 28:49.860
I have to be with you.

28:49.860 --> 28:50.860
That's all for now.

28:50.860 --> 28:51.860
Goodbye.

28:58.100 --> 29:06.740
Ladies and gentlemen, friends of Tennessee, I want to talk with you today about a new problem

29:06.740 --> 29:09.540
with which our generation is faced.

29:09.540 --> 29:15.340
Mankind is on the very verge of what may prove to be the most dramatic breakthrough in history,

29:15.340 --> 29:20.700
ranking even beyond the immense consequences of his discovery of the new world.

29:20.700 --> 29:24.540
I'm speaking of course of the venture into outer space.

29:24.540 --> 29:29.020
Soviet Union has sent two satellites orbiting around the earth.

29:29.020 --> 29:33.780
We too are entering this into space with missiles and satellites.

29:33.780 --> 29:41.860
The spaceship of science fiction, the space platforms are no longer wild figments of imagination.

29:41.860 --> 29:47.620
Nationally this creates a whole new area of international problems sooner or later.

29:47.620 --> 29:52.100
And I think it should be sooner during the infancy of this new age.

29:52.100 --> 29:57.060
We will have to set up the rules by which there will be some regulation of the exploration

29:57.060 --> 29:58.940
of outer space.

29:58.940 --> 30:02.860
It would be a great shame perhaps mankind's greatest failure.

30:02.860 --> 30:08.540
If man's wars and man's ills were extended to whatever area, he may eventually reach

30:08.540 --> 30:11.220
in the far reaches of space.

30:11.220 --> 30:16.900
Certainly we should be able to make up for many of our failures on the earth by coming

30:16.900 --> 30:23.860
to firm agreements to explore and if possible to develop these new and ever-reaching frontiers

30:23.860 --> 30:28.580
in peaceful cooperation and for peaceful ends.

30:28.580 --> 30:33.180
Men have of course space problems not entirely disassembly before.

30:33.180 --> 30:36.180
We have rules for the use of the high seas.

30:36.180 --> 30:40.700
All nations have found these rules advantageous and follow them.

30:40.700 --> 30:46.380
Despite the fact that modern weapons, navies and aircraft make possible extension of control

30:46.380 --> 30:53.500
of adjacent high seas far beyond the accepted three mile limit of any nation's sovereignty.

30:53.500 --> 31:00.460
Following the advent of the airplane, we extended by common national sovereignty, consent,

31:00.460 --> 31:03.660
into space above all of our nations.

31:03.660 --> 31:09.580
However as a practical matter, sovereignty as we know it can be extended only where it

31:09.580 --> 31:11.620
can be enforced.

31:11.620 --> 31:17.060
It is unlikely that there will ever be any means to control objects which move beyond

31:17.060 --> 31:19.580
and around the earth's orbit.

31:19.580 --> 31:26.020
The advantage is therefore of agreement on basic rules for a space exploration right now

31:26.020 --> 31:30.540
before mankind is made such an adventure become very obvious.

31:30.540 --> 31:35.740
It would be my hope that no one or three nations will make an effort to hog space through

31:35.740 --> 31:38.060
the exclusion of all others.

31:38.060 --> 31:43.260
I hope that many nations can approach the exploration of space cooperatively and that

31:43.260 --> 31:48.460
nation and that small nations as well as large and powerful ones can have a share in this

31:48.460 --> 31:50.580
endeavor.

31:50.580 --> 31:54.180
Experience indicates that we are not going to be able to make agreements with the Soviet

31:54.180 --> 31:59.300
Union which will establish peace in any one grand design.

31:59.300 --> 32:04.640
I think the fact that we agreed upon the exchange of students and other peoples with the

32:04.640 --> 32:10.080
Soviet Union just the other day showed that you can do it a piecemeal and little by

32:10.080 --> 32:11.080
little.

32:11.080 --> 32:15.680
I do believe that there are limited areas in which we can reach other agreements and this

32:15.680 --> 32:18.240
is one in which we ought to try.

32:18.240 --> 32:23.920
Let us make a sincere effort to obtain an agreement with the Soviet Union looking toward

32:23.920 --> 32:29.040
the United Nations leadership and laying down the rules and conditions for exploration

32:29.040 --> 32:35.400
of space, rules which will respect the right and hopes of the people of all nations.

32:35.400 --> 32:42.000
The United Nations is the only body that I know of which could do this and if the UN had

32:42.000 --> 32:47.480
nothing else to its credit and of course it has a great deal many things to its credit.

32:47.480 --> 32:53.240
The opportunity and the challenge to perfect and maintain peaceful penetration and exploration

32:53.240 --> 32:57.840
by man of outer space would be enough justification for its existence.

32:58.800 --> 33:02.760
I hope that the administration will move boldly into this field.

33:02.760 --> 33:08.160
I hope it makes known its desire to the Soviet Union and through the United States representative

33:08.160 --> 33:10.000
to the nations of all of the world.

33:10.000 --> 33:16.360
Of our desire not to control space but to share in its exploration and development with

33:16.360 --> 33:20.680
all other nations under a body of international law.

33:20.680 --> 33:25.800
I believe that this is something that should be done soon because sooner or later all

33:25.800 --> 33:31.360
nations will be laying out this claim and that claim and there is bound to be a conflict

33:31.360 --> 33:34.680
unless we do have some rules and regulations.

33:34.680 --> 33:39.560
The United States by taking the lead I think could gain much respect and goodwill among

33:39.560 --> 33:42.400
the people of the smaller nations of the earth.

33:42.400 --> 33:44.400
Thank you and goodbye until next week.

33:44.400 --> 33:56.000
Ladies and gentlemen, friends of Tennessee.

33:56.000 --> 34:02.120
I wanted to talk with you today about the current work in which I am engaged as chairman

34:02.120 --> 34:07.120
of the Senate Committee on any trust and monopoly legislation.

34:07.120 --> 34:12.960
Everyone with whom I talk these days is concerned greatly about the current business recession

34:12.960 --> 34:17.440
and most certainly this is true in Tennessee where unemployment has been rising in the

34:17.440 --> 34:23.720
cities and where the farmers who are using the hit first in these recessions and are suffering

34:23.720 --> 34:25.760
real hardships.

34:25.760 --> 34:31.240
Now along with Senators Eastland, Fulbright in Sammington, I have sponsored legislation designed

34:31.240 --> 34:37.240
to loosen the tight credit restrictions on farmers so they can get back on their feet.

34:37.240 --> 34:42.280
We have been partially successful thus far and we intend to keep on working at this until

34:42.280 --> 34:44.440
we are fully successful.

34:44.440 --> 34:50.080
We haven't had very much cooperation from the Secretary of Agriculture, Mr. Benson.

34:50.080 --> 34:55.760
So this week we took our cause and presented it to the White House where we hope to get

34:55.760 --> 34:57.920
a little better cooperation.

34:57.920 --> 35:02.760
The situation is really bad in Tennessee particularly in the western part of the vomitting

35:02.760 --> 35:03.760
state.

35:03.760 --> 35:09.800
I am interested in proposals which will spur needed public improvement and thereby give

35:09.800 --> 35:12.120
additional employment in the cities.

35:12.120 --> 35:19.120
However these things we all admit are to the economy what a tough hill is to adopt.

35:19.120 --> 35:25.000
They give you a boost but they neither diagnose, nor cure the underlying knowledge.

35:25.000 --> 35:30.640
Our committee has been at work a long time, pains taking the trying to diagnose one part

35:30.640 --> 35:34.080
of what we believe to be a fundamental topic.

35:34.080 --> 35:40.360
What is or any trust laws really working in a way which will encourage full production,

35:40.360 --> 35:45.680
full employment, full flowering of our productive pre-entipized economy.

35:45.680 --> 35:49.680
Do they really encourage competition?

35:49.680 --> 35:53.920
We examine this problem in one of our basic industries, steel.

35:53.920 --> 35:59.560
We found very little evidence of real competition there and now we are examining this same problem

35:59.560 --> 36:03.560
in another basic industry, automobile.

36:03.560 --> 36:09.000
What happens to the automobile industry is our transcending importance to all of us because

36:09.000 --> 36:15.240
one out of every seven persons in the United States depend either directly or indirectly

36:15.240 --> 36:18.800
on the automobile industry or a livelihood.

36:18.800 --> 36:23.480
Let me show you two charts which we have been studying in our hearing.

36:23.480 --> 36:30.320
This chart shows the situation in the automobile industry with general motors as of the first

36:30.320 --> 36:36.240
of this year having more than 50% of all of the automobiles making that net.

36:36.240 --> 36:44.320
A forward about 25%, a Chrysler about 17%, and the American motors and student-backed

36:44.320 --> 36:47.840
record making only about 3%.

36:47.840 --> 36:51.840
Only really three industries in the automobile industry.

36:51.840 --> 36:58.400
You will see by this chart that general motors has a very dominant position as a leader and

36:58.400 --> 37:04.000
there is really very little competition in the farest place between the big three.

37:04.000 --> 37:09.320
Now here is another chart that shows this position of general motors of the total value

37:09.320 --> 37:13.680
of shipments and the transportation vehicles.

37:13.680 --> 37:18.040
Take locomotive, for instance, they are just in automobiles, they are in a lot of other

37:18.040 --> 37:19.040
things.

37:19.040 --> 37:22.040
locomotive, almost 70%.

37:22.040 --> 37:24.840
locomotives switching type about 50%.

37:24.840 --> 37:40.680
Now these charts show the part of the problem that we find that is an unbalanced concentration

37:40.680 --> 37:41.680
of economic power.

37:41.680 --> 37:46.880
Whether this is good or bad for the country the committee has not yet said.

37:46.880 --> 37:49.720
Our studies are still in their early stage.

37:49.720 --> 37:54.120
But this we do know that the results as of now are not good.

37:54.120 --> 37:59.240
For end industries we have studied production is down and way down.

37:59.240 --> 38:00.640
This is certainly true of steel.

38:00.640 --> 38:04.640
For only 55% of our steel capacity is being used.

38:04.640 --> 38:10.800
It is true of automobile and of course this results in a great deal of unemployment.

38:10.800 --> 38:17.160
We in the United States cannot maintain our place in the world here on this earth and

38:17.160 --> 38:23.960
we cannot compete with the Soviets and trade and must be utilized our own productive genius

38:23.960 --> 38:25.760
at 12 capacity.

38:25.760 --> 38:30.040
We are not doing that when our basic industries are running at half-drawling.

38:30.040 --> 38:33.160
What we have got to do is to push the throttle forward.

38:33.160 --> 38:51.680
Thank you and goodbye and we will next week.

38:51.680 --> 38:56.920
The ladies and gentlemen, friends of Tennessee, a proposal which I have previously discussed

38:56.920 --> 39:01.360
with you on this program, got a fine push forward this week.

39:01.360 --> 39:06.040
Last fall you will remember I attended the NATO Parliamentarians conference as a member

39:06.040 --> 39:08.640
of the United States delegation.

39:08.640 --> 39:12.800
The conference composed of representatives of parliament and congresses of all of the

39:12.800 --> 39:17.480
NATO nations met in the NATO headquarters in Paris.

39:17.480 --> 39:21.640
They honored me by electing me chairman of the political committee.

39:21.640 --> 39:27.320
This political committee proposed a resolution which I feel is a long step forward in our

39:27.320 --> 39:32.920
constant search for ways and means by which we may obtain a more durable method of assuring

39:32.920 --> 39:33.920
peace.

39:33.920 --> 39:39.520
The committee proposed a resolution recommending that the NATO governments bring about a conference

39:39.520 --> 39:46.000
composed of leading representatives citizens of the various countries selected on a nonpartisan

39:46.000 --> 39:50.600
basis and directed to convenes often as necessary.

39:50.600 --> 39:55.960
In order to examine and to recommend how greater cooperation and unity of purpose within

39:55.960 --> 39:59.040
the Atlantic community may be developed.

39:59.040 --> 40:04.800
Now what is the need of such a conference and what might we hope that it would accomplish?

40:04.800 --> 40:09.480
The need is evident every time that you pick up the paper to read and read of another

40:09.480 --> 40:10.800
answer to it.

40:10.800 --> 40:16.040
In NATO we have all agreed that the defense of one of us is important to the survival of

40:16.040 --> 40:17.040
all of us.

40:17.600 --> 40:22.720
Yet we frequently find occasions when our various nations are going along separate paths and

40:22.720 --> 40:25.240
in the version direction.

40:25.240 --> 40:28.080
Such an occasion was Suez crisis.

40:28.080 --> 40:31.360
The Tunisian arms incident of last year.

40:31.360 --> 40:33.640
The Hungarian revolution.

40:33.640 --> 40:38.840
And just this week when French planes bombed the Tunisian border town.

40:38.840 --> 40:43.240
An act which could have serious repercussions in the United Nations.

40:43.240 --> 40:46.720
And in which unfortunately American planes were used.

40:46.720 --> 40:49.360
We had a new example of this problem.

40:49.360 --> 40:55.080
The problem therefore is to work out some method by which we could have some prior consultation

40:55.080 --> 40:58.600
and consideration before these acts are committed.

40:58.600 --> 41:03.560
Some method by which we can be sure that we are all going in the same political and economic

41:03.560 --> 41:04.560
direction.

41:04.560 --> 41:11.360
For without common purposes we will not be, we will not long be militarily our scientific

41:11.360 --> 41:12.360
allies.

41:12.920 --> 41:17.480
Now the governments have worked on this on a government-to-government basis for a long

41:17.480 --> 41:18.480
time.

41:18.480 --> 41:21.960
We members of parliament and Congresses have worked at it.

41:21.960 --> 41:26.520
But I frankly don't think that we are going to be solved unless we bring about the best

41:26.520 --> 41:30.280
minds of all of our nations among our citizens.

41:30.280 --> 41:35.520
We can speak freely because they would not be officially representing their governments.

41:35.520 --> 41:40.920
Also to bear in this really thoroughgoing study of this problem.

41:40.920 --> 41:46.120
We would hope to accomplish the means by which unity of action might be achieved.

41:46.120 --> 41:53.280
This week, Theodore Francis Green of Rhode Island, the Senate Chairman of the Senate Committee

41:53.280 --> 41:58.600
on Foreign Relations, introduced a resolution in the Senate calling upon the President to

41:58.600 --> 42:03.080
implement our resolution and to help bring about this conference.

42:03.080 --> 42:08.840
I joined Senator Green in his resolution and he was also joined by Senator Solvenstole

42:08.840 --> 42:14.400
Massachusetts in Javits of New York, both Republicans and by Senator Henry Jackson and

42:14.400 --> 42:16.400
Washington and Democrat.

42:16.400 --> 42:22.040
I am hopeful that with this display of important and bipartisan interests in the proposal which

42:22.040 --> 42:27.600
are committed tariffs and which was unanimously approved there by the delegates of all of

42:27.600 --> 42:32.280
the NATO nations that the conference will be called this year.

42:32.280 --> 42:37.360
There is one other thing that I wanted to mention on this occasion.

42:37.360 --> 42:42.680
All of us became have become concerned by the new evidence that all is not well with

42:42.680 --> 42:45.320
our economy domestically.

42:45.320 --> 42:52.920
In the face of a rise in January of 1,100,000 unemployed, the post-mester general announced

42:52.920 --> 42:58.080
that post office modernization program to make work an employment.

42:58.080 --> 43:02.360
And the President said that other things will be done if the picture doesn't change next

43:02.360 --> 43:03.680
month.

43:03.680 --> 43:08.380
I want to say that one of the best things the President could do in the far as I region

43:08.380 --> 43:14.200
is concerned would be to really get behind the TVA self-financing bill and help pass it

43:14.200 --> 43:16.720
in the House of Representatives.

43:16.720 --> 43:22.000
Then we could start building steam plants and at no cost whatever to the federal government.

43:22.000 --> 43:27.120
And in addition to the work of building these steam plants, we would have a continuing economic

43:27.120 --> 43:33.440
spur to the economy through the years which comes from having adequate electric power.

43:33.440 --> 43:40.440
Thank you and goodbye until next week.

